{"bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":0,"note":"# Let's tackle the task of creating an identity matrix using NumPy.\n\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Function to create and print an identity matrix of size N\ndef create_and_print_identity_matrix(N):\n    # Use NumPy's eye function to create an identity matrix of size N\n    identity_matrix = np.eye(N)\n    # Return the identity matrix\n    return identity_matrix\n\n# Example usage for N=3\n# In a Jupyter Notebook, you would replace this with user input\nN_example = 3\n\n# Call the function and print the output\ncreate_and_print_identity_matrix(N_example)\n\n————\n\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef create_and_print_identity_matrix(N):\n    identity_matrix = np.eye(N)\n    return identity_matrix\n\nN_example = 3\ncreate_and_print_identity_matrix(N_example)\n"}